				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203733" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1393437888 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Feb 2014 18:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1978566">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Most confusing to me, the very existence of new GOC as a fairly paranormal-tolerant UN-backed organization calls into question why the SCPF is permitted to exist (independently) at all. I may be stretching here, but if they're willing to seek diplomatic relations with Eugenio of all things then the Foundations is arguably guilty of war crimes at minimum- and much worse when shit like Tophet or Montauk is brought into consideration.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Gentlemen. We have an organization here that is guilty of war crimes and crimes against humanity. They must be stopped.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Where are they located?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;All over the world, but mostly ███████.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Damn. That's a Security Council nation. Make an official request through the proper channels?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;We tried. The ambassador said, probably quite truthfully, that he does not know what we are talking about.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I guess that rules out trying to get the international community to put pressure on them. It's not like we can tell the world governments why we should sanction ███████ because they're harboring a known human rights violator. Can we send a STRIKE team? Do this quietly?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Second Mission concerns. The organization is too deeply entrenched. First Mission concerns besides&#8230; despite what they're doing, they're maintaining containment of these parathreats. I can't guarantee that we can do the same. Especially during the strike. Too risky, we could lose control of the parathreat and end up in an EES.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Stupid Eschatological Event Sequences. All right. Keep monitoring them. Make a list of their human rights violations. Our hands are tied for now, but we'll keep this in mind for the day we go Pizzicato.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I'll add it to the big list.&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
