<p>My personal guess - and this is speaking as both a newbie to the wider Foundation, and to the GOC canon - is that the Foundation has a more research-orientated focus, and that is where its &quot;edge&quot; among the supernatural community comes from. Like, the GOC can complain about the Foundation's unethical treatment of D-class personnel - and those are some really valid points - but at the end of the day they won't have as much data on how the supernatural interacts with baseline human while we do.</p>

